<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,464,367,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">Differential diagnosis:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[472,658,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Lonchaeidae" genus="Lonchaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vanua">
<emphasis box="[472,658,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">Lonchaea vanua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the smallest of the 
<taxonomicName box="[908,1018,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Lonchaeidae" genus="Lonchaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[908,1018,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">Lonchaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species known from 
<taxonomicName box="[1261,1303,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Lonchaeidae" genus="Lonchaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="551" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fiji">
<collectingCountry box="[1261,1303,367,392]" name="Fiji" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">Fiji</collectingCountry>
</taxonomicName>
, the hairing on the arista is also the shortest of the four species. The male genitalia are distinct due to the row of long setulae present on the inner surface of the surstyli.
</paragraph>
